text: Rick Gundrum is an American politician and businessman. Gundrum lives in Slinger, Wisconsin and is the owner of McKay Enterprises, an audio-visual company. Gundrum served on the Slinger Village Board and on the Washington County Board of Supervisors. He served as chairman of the county board. Gundrum was elected to the Wisconsin Assembly in a special election on January 15, 2018 replacing Bob Gannon who died while in office in October 2017.
